-- Iberia sells Amadeus stake for 578 million euros
-- By Tracy Rucinski
-- Thu Jul 31, 2014 12:38PM EDT
-- None



MADRID, July 31 (Reuters) - Spanish airline Iberia is selling its stake in Madrid-based travel technology company Amadeus <AMA.MC>, held through derivatives, to Nomura for 578 million euros ($774 million), the International Airlines Group (IAG) <ICAG.L> said on Thursday.

